US.06 Create Events (File 2)

1. Login with an approved Organizer account.
You can login with the following credentials:

Organizer ID: O12345

Password: 12345

Expected result:
Organizer dashboard loads with organization name and event management options.

2. Open the Create Event page from the sidebar.

Expected result:
A form is displayed allowing the organizer to enter event details such as:

Event Title

Category

Date & Time

Location

Capacity

Event Type

Event Banner (image)

Description 


3. Fill in valid event details (example):

Event Name: “AI & Machine Learning Talk”

Description: “A workshop hosted by Tech Club introducing machine learning basics.”

Date: 2025-02-10

Time: 18:00

Location: Hall A

Capacity: 100

Expected result:
The form accepts the input. No error messages are shown.

4. Click the Create Event button.

Expected result:

The system validates the inputs

A success message appears:
“Event created successfully.”

The new event is added to the event list on the organizer dashboard

The event becomes visible on the student Browse Events page

5. If you try to submit the form with missing required fields (e.g., empty event name or missing date)

Expected result:

The system rejects the submission

Required fields are highlighted

Error message displayed:
“Please fill all required fields.”

No event is created

6. If you try submitting invalid data (e.g., text in ticket count field or negative numbers)

Expected result:

System prevents submission

Error shown:
“Please enter a valid number of tickets.”

No crash

Upload an event image (optional).

Expected result:

Image preview appears

File uploads successfully

Event can still be created with or without image
